content.text: Hi there—how can I help you today?

## My request for Codex:
中文跟我交互，当前系统仍沿用旧有的数据契约：Planner 输出 draft_reply、PlanStep 列表，Orchestrator 依赖该草稿并触发 KB 查询，Reception 再用 “Professional draft reply” 润色。我刚刚重写了提示词（请你认真阅读D:\AI_Projects\Kobe\TelegramBot\config\PromptConfig.yaml以理解当前的设定，并且禁止修改该文件，必须以该文件为基准来实现代码变更来满足该文件提示词要求的流程），使 Planner 只产出分析、KB Agent 给出方案，但代码尚未同步更新。日志和文档仍是旧流程，token 计数也统计草稿长度。这导致提示词与代码不匹配，无法实现新的“Planner→KB→Reception”职责划分。当前任务需要按计划全量重写 Planner、KB Agent、Reception、Orchestrator、基类和相关 prompt，改用新的 JSON 架构，并保持 RichLogger 的 DEBUG 级别输出。
请你阅读telegrambot代码库，理解当前情况，然后更新代码，直接重写相应的py文件，避免多步修改反复阅读（但是禁止丢失原有的接口契约等，必要时请你浏览openai response API python SDK官方网站内容，以及社区方案，确保实现时符合最新的也时正确的，当前时2025年10月24日，你的知识库停留在2024年，而我们需要的内容是近期刚出的）
开发计划：重构 Planner → KB → Reception 流程（全量重写核心文件）

总体架构

目标：Planner 仅产出“分析+缺口+KB 请求”，KB Agent 根据 Planner 提供的上下文给出完整方案，Reception 负责润色＆追问用户。
核心文件将全部重新编写（删掉重写）：
TelegramBot/agents/base.py、TelegramBot/agents/planner_agent.py、TelegramBot/agents/orchestrator.py、TelegramBot/agents/visa_kb_agent.py、TelegramBot/agents/reception_agent.py、TelegramBot/token_meter.py（结构输出更新）、TelegramBot/config/PromptConfig.yaml（只保留最终结构示例）、config/PromptStructureExample.md（保持文档同步）。
数据契约定义（写在 base.py 新版里）

PlannerAnalysis:
{
  "status": "ok|need_more_info|escalate",
  "customer_goal": "...",
  "known_facts": ["..."],
  "knowledge_gaps": ["..."],
  "user_questions": ["..."],          # 要让 Reception 去问用户
  "kb_queries": [
    {
      "query": "...",                 # 单一主题
      "context": "...",               # Planner提供给KB的背景
      "filters": {},
      "priority": "high|medium|low"
    }
  ],
  "notes": "内部提醒，可选"
}
KBResponsePayload（Visa KB Agent 输出）：
{
  "business_summary": "...",
  "recommendations": ["..."],         # 可执行步骤
  "document_checklist": ["..."],
  "risk_notes": ["..."],
  "follow_up_questions": ["..."],     # 需补充信息
  "sources": [{"path": "...", "title": "...", "excerpt": "..."}]
}
PlannerOutcome（base.py）：
@dataclass
class PlannerOutcome:
    analysis: PlannerAnalysis
    kb_responses: List[KBAnswer]   # 每条含 structured payload + 摘要文本
    status: str                    # 同 analysis.status
    debug_info: Dict[str, Any]
KBAnswer 增强：加入 structured: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]。
Planner 重写（planner_agent.py）

_build_messages 仍传 reception + intent + user_story。
parse_response 使用新的 PlannerAnalysisModel (pydantic)。
不再返回 reply；仅返回 PlannerOutcome(analysis=..., kb_responses=[], status=analysis.status, debug_info=...)。
token_meter 记账调整：记录 analysis 的长度、缺口数量、kb_queries 数等。
KB Agent 重写（visa_kb_agent.py）

接口 run(query_bundle: KBQueryBundle)，其中 bundle 包含 Planner analysis、单条 query、filters 等。
prompt 接受 planner_context（goal/known/gaps/user_questions）。
parse_response 使用 KBResponsePayloadModel；回填到 KBAnswer(structured=payload.model_dump(), answer=_format_text(...))。
保留工具调用逻辑，日志使用 RichLogger（level=DEBUG），控制台与文件都输出。
Orchestrator 重写（orchestrator.py）

Planner 返回 PlannerOutcome（analysis-only）。
遍历 analysis.kb_queries 调用 KB Agent；收集 KBAnswer list 填回 outcome.kb_responses。
状态处理：若 Planner 标记 need_more_info 且无 kb_queries，就走 Reception 询问用户；若 KB 失败，记录 fallback 在 outcome.debug_info["kb_failures"]。
不再引用 PlanStep；删除对应 dataclass &逻辑。
保持 _execute_kb_actions（新函数）写盘日志：每次 KB 请求记录 query/context/filters 及结果摘要。
Reception 重写（reception_agent.py）

craft_reply 构建 prompt：
Planner analysis：goal、已知、缺口、user_questions
KB responses：business_summary、recommendations、follow_up_questions 等
需要 LLM 输出最终回复 + 需要追问的内容（保持现有 ReceptionReplyResult 结构）。
如果 Planner 无 user_questions & KB 无 follow_up，则输出直接给用户的说明；若 analysis.user_questions 非空，提示 LLM 必须礼貌追问。
记录 token_meter stage：标记使用的 KB 模型、analysis 条数。
token_meter.py 更新

需要新的 stage label：
PLANNER ANALYSIS
KB LOOKUP #{n}
RECEPTION REPLY
StageUsage.note 中包含 JSON 摘要（goal/缺口数/问答数），保持 RichLogger DEBUG 输出。
PromptConfig.yaml 重写

仅保留最新 prompt：intent_router.system（不变）、planner.system（描述新结构并列出 JSON 字段）、visa_kb.system（明确输出键名）、reception.reply（引用 analysis+kb_responses）。
删除过期备注、旧 schema。
PromptStructureExample.md 重写

新增一个完整示例：
Planner 输出 JSON 示例
KB Agent 输出 JSON 示例
Reception prompt &最终话术示例
Redis 状态更新说明（user_story 如何包含 Planner 的 notes / KB recommendations）。
保持 RichLogger 打印示例。
测试与验证

编写 tests/test_planner_pipeline.py（伪造 Planner LLM 输出 -> ensure Pydantic parse）。
编写 tests/test_kb_payload.py（验证结构化输出 -> KBAnswer struct）。
使用 pytest -k planner_pipeline 运行。
手动 uvicorn app:app 启动一次，调一条业务消息，观察日志：
每个 stage 都有 DEBUG 输出
Planner analysis 结构正确
KB structured 有 recommendations
Reception 生成追问/答复。
日志要求
所有重写文件顶部统一 logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node(..., level=logging.DEBUG)。
在 Planner / KB / Reception 关键分支前后打 DEBUG log（目标、缺口、查询数量、推荐条数）。
保留 console 输出（RichLogger 本身会双写 console + file）。
最终提交前检查
mypy TelegramBot/agents（确认 dataclass/pydantic 类型）。
ruff check or flake8 保持风格。
git status 确认只新增/重写上述文件及测试。
README 或 CHANGELOG 更新“Planner 角色调整”说明。
按照以上命令式步骤，在下一个窗口中直接重写每个文件即可，避免逐段 patch 造成老逻辑残留。

I’m also aware I might need to browse the OpenAI API docs for up-to-date info and will prepare to use web.run if necessary.

{"output":"from __future__ import annotations

from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import Any, Dict, Iterable, List, Optional


@dataclass
class AgentMessage:
    """Minimal representation of a chat turn."""

    role: str
    content: str
    timestamp: Optional[str] = None


@dataclass
class AgentContext:
    """Information about the current conversation."""

    bot_id: int
    chat_id: int
    user_id: int
    chat_type: str
    username: Optional[str]
    historical_user_messages: List[AgentMessage] = field(default_factory=list)
    last_assistant_message: Optional[AgentMessage] = None
    current_user_message: Optional[AgentMessage] = None
    user_story: Optional[str] = None

    @classmethod
    def from_conversation(
        cls,
        *,
        bot_id: int,
        chat_id: int,
        user_id: int,
        chat_type: str,
        username: Optional[str],
        historical_user_messages: Iterable[Dict[str, Any]],
        last_assistant_message: Optional[Dict[str, Any]],
        current_user_message: Dict[str, Any],
        user_story: Optional[str],
    ) -> "AgentContext":
        def to_message(entry: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]) -> Optional[AgentMessage]:
            if entry is None:
                return None
            return AgentMessage(
                role=str(entry.get("role", "")),
                content=str(entry.get("content", "")),
                timestamp=entry.get("timestamp"),
            )

        history_messages = [
            to_message(item) for item in historical_user_messages
        ]
        filtered_history = [msg for msg in history_messages if msg is not None]

        return cls(
            bot_id=bot_id,
            chat_id=chat_id,
            user_id=user_id,
            chat_type=chat_type,
            username=username,
            historical_user_messages=filtered_history,
            last_assistant_message=to_message(last_assistant_message),
            current_user_message=to_message(current_user_message),
            user_story=user_story,
        )


@dataclass
class ReceptionResult:
    """What the intake agent hands to downstream agents."""

    user_message: AgentMessage
    historical_user_messages: List[AgentMessage]
    last_assistant_message: Optional[AgentMessage]
    conversation_preamble: str
    user_story: Optional[str]


@dataclass
class IntentDecision:
    """Structured decision emitted by the intent agent."""

    route: Optional[str]
    confidence: float
    needs_kb: bool
    filters: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
    raw_response: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None


@dataclass
class KBQuery:
    """Single KB query to be executed by the knowledge agent."""

    query: str
    context: str = ""
    filters: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    priority: str = "medium"

    def __post_init__(self) -> None:
        self.query = (self.query or "").strip()
        self.context = (self.context or "").strip()
        if self.priority not in {"high", "medium", "low"}:
            self.priority = "medium"


@dataclass
class PlannerAnalysis:
    """Planner structured reasoning shared across the pipeline."""

    status: str
    customer_goal: str
    known_facts: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    knowledge_gaps: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    user_questions: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    kb_queries: List[KBQuery] = field(default_factory=list)
    notes: Optional[str] = None


@dataclass
class KBSourceReference:
    """Canonical reference to a knowledge base document."""

    path: str
    title: Optional[str] = None
    excerpt: Optional[str] = None


@dataclass
class KBResponsePayload:
    """Structured payload emitted by the KB agent."""

    business_summary: str
    recommendations: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    document_checklist: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    risk_notes: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    follow_up_questions: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    sources: List[KBSourceReference] = field(default_factory=list)


@dataclass
class KBAnswer:
    """Response coming back from the knowledge base agent."""

    answer: Optional[str]
    sources: List[Dict[str, Any]] = field(default_factory=list)
    metadata: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    structured: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None


@dataclass
class KBQueryBundle:
    """Execution bundle combining planner analysis with a specific KB query."""

    analysis: PlannerAnalysis
    query: KBQuery
    index: int = 1
    total: int = 1

from __future__ import annotations

import logging
import json
from typing import Any, Dict, List, Literal, Optional, Union

from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field

from TelegramBot.config.prompt_loader import get_prompt
from TelegramBot.config.model_config import get_model_name
from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
from TelegramBot.openai_runtime import get_usage_snapshot, parse_response
from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
from TelegramBot import token_meter

from .base import (
    AgentContext,
    BaseAgent,
    ReceptionResult,
    IntentDecision,
    PlanStep,
    PlannerOutcome,
)

logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.planner", level=logging.DEBUG)

HISTORY_SLICE = 8


# ---------- Pydantic models describing the structured planner output ----------


class KBQueryPayload(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", json_schema_extra={"additionalProperties": False})

    query: str
    filters: Dict[str, str] | None = None
    notes: Optional[str] = None
    context: Optional[str] = None
    follow_up_key: Optional[str] = None


class AskUserPayload(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", json_schema_extra={"additionalProperties": False})

    question: str
    notes: Optional[str] = None
    context: Optional[str] = None
    follow_up_key: Optional[str] = None


class KBQueryAction(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", json_schema_extra={"additionalProperties": False})

    type: Literal["kb_query"] = "kb_query"
    payload: KBQueryPayload


class AskUserAction(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", json_schema_extra={"additionalProperties": False})

    type: Literal["ask_user"] = "ask_user"
    payload: AskUserPayload


PlannerAction = Union[KBQueryAction, AskUserAction]


class PlannerPlan(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", json_schema_extra={"additionalProperties": False})

    status: str = Field(pattern=r"^(ok|need_more_info|escalate)$")
    draft_reply: str
    notes: str = ""
    questions: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
    actions: List[PlannerAction] = Field(default_factory=list)

from __future__ import annotations

import logging
from statistics import mean
from datetime import datetime, timezone
from typing import Dict, List, Literal, Optional

from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field

from TelegramBot.config.prompt_loader import get_prompt
from TelegramBot.config.model_config import get_model_name
from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
from TelegramBot.openai_runtime import get_usage_snapshot, parse_response
from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
from TelegramBot import token_meter

from .base import AgentContext, AgentMessage, BaseAgent, ReceptionResult, PlannerOutcome

logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.reception", level=logging.DEBUG)

def _now_iso() -> str:
    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(timespec="seconds")


class ReceptionAgent(BaseAgent):
    """Reception persona responsible for greeting users and delivering final responses."""

    def __init__(
        self,
        *,
        max_history_messages: int = 50,
        reply_temperature: float = 0.85,
    ) -> None:
        self.max_history_messages = max_history_messages
        self.config = get_config()
        self.reply_temperature = reply_temperature
        self.reply_prompt = get_prompt("reception.reply")

    async def run(self, context: AgentContext, user_message: str) -> ReceptionResult:
        historical_users = (
            context.historical_user_messages[-self.max_history_messages :]
            if context.historical_user_messages
            else []
        )
        last_assistant = context.last_assistant_message
        current_user = context.current_user_message or AgentMessage(
            role="user", content=user_message, timestamp=_now_iso()
        )

        history_section = self._format_history_block(historical_users)
        last_assistant_section = self._format_message_line(last_assistant, "assistant")
        current_section = self._format_message_line(current_user, "user", label="current")

        preamble = (
            f"now: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}\n"
            f"user_story: {context.user_story or '(none)'}\n"
            "historical_user_messages:\n"
            f"{history_section}\n"
            "last_assistant_reply:\n"
            f"{last_assistant_section}\n"
            "current_user_message:\n"
            f"{current_section}"
        )

        return ReceptionResult(
            user_message=current_user,
            historical_user_messages=historical_users,
            last_assistant_message=last_assistant,
            conversation_preamble=preamble,

    def _format_message_line(
        self,
        message: Optional[AgentMessage],
        speaker: str,
        *,
        label: str = "historical",
    ) -> str:
        if message is None:
            return "  (none)"
        timestamp = message.timestamp or "unknown"
        return f"  - [{timestamp}] {label}.{speaker}: {message.content}"

    def _format_history_block(self, messages: List[AgentMessage]) -> str:
        if not messages:
            return "  (none)"
        return "\n".join(self._format_message_line(msg, "user") for msg in messages)

    def _build_timeline(self, reception: ReceptionResult) -> List[str]:
        timeline: List[str] = []
        for msg in reception.historical_user_messages[-6:]:
            timeline.append(self._format_message_line(msg, "user"))
        if reception.last_assistant_message:
            timeline.append(self._format_message_line(reception.last_assistant_message, "assistant"))
        return timeline

    def _summarize_user_story(
        self,
        context: AgentContext,
        reception: ReceptionResult,
        plan: PlannerOutcome,
    ) -> str:
        existing = context.user_story or ""

        messages = reception.historical_user_messages + [reception.user_message]
        lengths = [len(msg.content) for msg in messages if msg.content]
        avg_len = mean(lengths) if lengths else 0
        if avg_len >= 80:
            style = "\u504f\u8bdd\u75af"
        elif avg_len >= 40:
            style = "\u504f\u8be6\u5c3d"
        else:
            style = "\u8868\u8fbe\u7b80\u6d01"

        topic = plan.debug_info.get("notes") or reception.user_message.content
        topic = (topic or "").replace("\n", " ").strip() or "\u5c1a\u672a\u660e\u786e\u8bc9\u6c42"

        pending_questions = plan.debug_info.get("questions") or plan.debug_info.get("planner_raw", {}).get("questions")
        if isinstance(pending_questions, list):
            pending = ", ".join(str(q) for q in pending_questions if q)
        else:
            pending = ""

        story_parts = [
            f"\u98ce\u683c: {style}",
            f"\u4e3b\u8981\u8bc9\u6c42: {topic}",
        ]
        if pending:
            story_parts.append(f"\u5f85\u8865\u5145: {pending}")

        new_story = "; ".join(story_parts)
        if existing and existing != new_story:
            combined = f"{existing} | latest: {new_story}"
            if len(combined) > 600:
                combined = combined[-600:]
            return combined
        return new_story

def _tokens_to_cost(tokens: int, rate_per_1k: float) -> float:
    if rate_per_1k <= 0:
        return 0.0
    return (tokens / 1000.0) * rate_per_1k


def _resolve_pricing(model: str) -> Tuple[float, float]:
    cfg = get_config()
    overrides = getattr(cfg, "get_openai_pricing_table", None)
    pricing_table: Dict[str, Dict[str, float]] = {}
    if callable(overrides):
        pricing_table = overrides()

    if model in pricing_table:
        entry = pricing_table[model]
        return (
            float(entry.get("prompt", 0.0) or entry.get("input", 0.0) or 0.0),
            float(entry.get("completion", 0.0) or entry.get("output", 0.0) or 0.0),
        )

    for key, entry in pricing_table.items():
        if model.startswith(key):
            return (
                float(entry.get("prompt", 0.0) or entry.get("input", 0.0) or 0.0),
                float(entry.get("completion", 0.0) or entry.get("output", 0.0) or 0.0),
            )

    for prefix, rates in _DEFAULT_PRICING.items():
        if model.startswith(prefix):
            return rates

    return (0.0, 0.0)


def _truncate(text: str, limit: int = 200) -> str:
    stripped = text.strip()
    if len(stripped) <= limit:
        return stripped
    return stripped[: limit - 3] + "..."

def _print_stage_block(usage: StageUsage) -> None:
    border = '-' * FRAME_WIDTH
    ordinal = _ordinal(usage.order)
    title = f"+- [{ordinal}] {usage.label} "
    padding = max(FRAME_WIDTH - len(title) - 1, 0)
    logger.info(title + '-' * padding)
    logger.info("| MODEL: %s | TIME: %.2fs", usage.model, usage.duration_ms / 1000.0)
    logger.info(
        "| COST: tokens(%d->%d) $%.4f | len(%d->%d)",
        usage.prompt_tokens,
        usage.completion_tokens,
        usage.total_cost,
        usage.input_length,
        usage.output_length,
    )
    _print_multiline('INPUT', usage.input_preview)
    _print_multiline('OUTPUT', usage.output_preview)
    status_block = f"[{usage.status.upper()}]"
    if usage.note:
        logger.info("| STATUS: %s %s", status_block, usage.note)
    else:
        logger.info("| STATUS: %s", status_block)
    logger.info('+' + border)

def _ordinal(order: int) -> str:
    if order % 100 in (11, 12, 13):
        suffix = "th"
    else:
        suffix = {1: "st", 2: "nd", 3: "rd"}.get(order % 10, "th")
    return f"{order}{suffix}"


def _print_multiline(label: str, text: str) -> None:
    if not text:
        logger.info("| %s:", label)
        logger.info("|   (empty)")
        return
    lines = text.splitlines() or [text]
    logger.info("| %s: %s", label, lines[0])
    for line in lines[1:]:
        logger.info("|   %s", line)

def _log_divider(char: str = "-") -> None:
    logger.info(char * FRAME_WIDTH)

I'll ensure all definitions align with the new JSON specs, remove outdated classes like PlanStep, and integrate detailed token meter recording and debug logging. The orchestrator will coordinate flow based on planner analysis, and each module’s prompts and parsing logic will be updated accordingly. This will prepare the codebase for a thorough rewrite of all involved files with consistent data contracts and enhanced observability.

**Designing new prompt configurations and base definitions**

I'm planning to create streamlined new prompt files that keep the `intent_router.system` mostly unchanged as required, while crafting fresh, minimal prompts for planner, visa_kb, and reception stages aligned with the new architecture. Alongside, I'll rewrite the base dataclasses module to introduce updated data contracts, conversion helpers, and consistent docstrings, ensuring compatibility with the new Pydantic models and the overall pipeline redesign. This careful preparation will support a clean, comprehensive rewrite of the codebase.

+from __future__ import annotations
+
+from dataclasses import dataclass, field
+from typing import Any, Dict, Iterable, List, Optional
+
+
+@dataclass
+class AgentMessage:
+    """Minimal representation of a chat turn."""
+
+    role: str
+    content: str
+    timestamp: Optional[str] = None
+
+
+@dataclass
+class AgentContext:
+    """Information about the current conversation."""
+
+    bot_id: int
+    chat_id: int
+    user_id: int
+    chat_type: str
+    username: Optional[str]
+    historical_user_messages: List[AgentMessage] = field(default_factory=list)
+    last_assistant_message: Optional[AgentMessage] = None
+    current_user_message: Optional[AgentMessage] = None
+    user_story: Optional[str] = None
+
+    @classmethod
+    def from_conversation(
+        cls,
+        *,
+        bot_id: int,
+        chat_id: int,
+        user_id: int,
+        chat_type: str,
+        username: Optional[str],
+        historical_user_messages: Iterable[Dict[str, Any]],
+        last_assistant_message: Optional[Dict[str, Any]],
+        current_user_message: Dict[str, Any],
+        user_story: Optional[str],
+    ) -> "AgentContext":
+        """Build an AgentContext from raw dictionary payloads."""
+
+        def to_message(entry: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]) -> Optional[AgentMessage]:
+            if entry is None:
+                return None
+            return AgentMessage(
+                role=str(entry.get("role", "")),
+                content=str(entry.get("content", "")),
+                timestamp=entry.get("timestamp"),
+            )
+
+        history_messages = [
+            to_message(item) for item in historical_user_messages
+        ]
+        filtered_history = [msg for msg in history_messages if msg is not None]
+
+        return cls(
+            bot_id=bot_id,
+            chat_id=chat_id,
+            user_id=user_id,
+            chat_type=chat_type,
+            username=username,
+            historical_user_messages=filtered_history,
+            last_assistant_message=to_message(last_assistant_message),
+            current_user_message=to_message(current_user_message),
+            user_story=user_story,
+        )
+
+
+@dataclass
+class ReceptionResult:
+    """What the intake agent hands to downstream agents."""
+
+    user_message: AgentMessage
+    historical_user_messages: List[AgentMessage]
+    last_assistant_message: Optional[AgentMessage]
+    conversation_preamble: str
+    user_story: Optional[str]
+
+
+@dataclass
+class IntentDecision:
+    """Structured decision emitted by the intent router agent."""
+
+    route: Optional[str]

+    needs_kb: bool
+    filters: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
+    raw_response: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
+
+
+@dataclass
+class KBQuery:
+    """Single KB query to be executed by the knowledge agent."""
+
+    query: str
+    context: str = ""
+    filters: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
+    priority: str = "medium"
+
+    def __post_init__(self) -> None:
+        self.query = (self.query or "").strip()
+        self.context = (self.context or "").strip()
+        if self.priority not in {"high", "medium", "low"}:
+            self.priority = "medium"
+
+
+@dataclass
+class PlannerAnalysis:
+    """Planner structured reasoning shared across the pipeline."""
+
+    status: str
+    customer_goal: str
+    known_facts: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)

+    def summary(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:

+            "knowledge_gaps": len(self.knowledge_gaps),

+            "kb_queries": len(self.kb_queries),
+            "has_notes": bool(self.notes),

+
+
+@dataclass
+class KBSourceReference:

+

+
+@dataclass

+@dataclass

+
+
+class BaseAgent:
+    """Common interface for all agents."""

*** Begin Patch
*** Add File: Kobe/TelegramBot/agents/planner_agent.py
+from __future__ import annotations
+
+import json
+import logging
+from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional
+
+from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field, ValidationError
+
+from TelegramBot.config.prompt_loader import get_prompt
+from TelegramBot.config.model_config import get_model_name
+from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
+from TelegramBot.openai_runtime import get_usage_snapshot, parse_response
+from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
+from TelegramBot import token_meter
+
+from .base import (
+    AgentContext,
+    BaseAgent,
+    IntentDecision,
+    KBQuery,
+    PlannerAnalysis,
+    PlannerOutcome,
+    ReceptionResult,
+)
+
+logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.planner", level=logging.DEBUG)
+
+HISTORY_SLICE = 8
+ALLOWED_STATUS = {"ok", "need_more_info", "escalate"}
+
+
+class PlannerKBQueryModel(BaseModel):
+    """Structured description of a single KB request emitted by the planner."""
+
+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")
+
+    query: str = Field(min_length=1, description="Single, focused KB query")
+    context: str = Field("", description="Planner-provided background for the KB agent")
+    filters: Dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict, description="Optional KB search filters")
+    priority: str = Field("medium", pattern=r"^(high|medium|low)$")
+
+
+class PlannerAnalysisModel(BaseModel):
+    """Model matching the LLM contract for planner outputs."""
+
+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")
+
+    status: str = Field(pattern=r"^(ok|need_more_info|escalate)$")
+    customer_goal: str
+    known_facts: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    knowledge_gaps: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    user_questions: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    kb_queries: List[PlannerKBQueryModel] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    notes: Optional[str] = None
+
+
+class PlannerAgent(BaseAgent):
+    """Turns intent decisions into structured analyses for downstream agents."""
+
+    def __init__(self, *, enable_kb: bool = True) -> None:
+        self.config = get_config()
+        self.enable_kb = enable_kb
+        self.system_prompt = get_prompt("planner.system")
+
+    async def run(
+        self,
+        context: AgentContext,
+        reception: ReceptionResult,
+        intent: IntentDecision,
+    ) -> PlannerOutcome:
+        usage_snapshot: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
+        parsed_model: Optional[PlannerAnalysisModel] = None
+        error_message: Optional[str] = None
+
+        messages = self._build_messages(reception, intent, context.user_story)
+        logger.debug("Planner messages constructed with %s history entries", len(reception.historical_user_messages))
+
+        try:
+            response, parsed = parse_response(
+                messages=messages,
+                model=get_model_name("planner", default=self.config.openai_model, bot_key=str(context.bot_id)),
+                response_format=PlannerAnalysisModel,
+                temperature=0.15,
+                usage_label="planner",
+            )
+            usage_snapshot = get_usage_snapshot(response)
+            parsed_model = self._coerce_model(parsed)
+        except ValidationError as exc:
+            logger.warning("Planner structured validation failed: %s", exc)
+            error_message = str(exc)
+        except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive guard
+            logger.error("Planner call failed, falling back to safe analysis: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
+            error_message = str(exc)
+
+        analysis = self._build_analysis(parsed_model, reception, error_message)
+        outcome = PlannerOutcome(
+            analysis=analysis,
+            kb_responses=[],
+            status=analysis.status,
+            debug_info=self._compose_debug_info(parsed_model, intent, error_message),
+        )
+
+        logger.debug(
+            "Planner analysis ready: status=%s gaps=%d kb_queries=%d user_questions=%d",
+            analysis.status,
+            len(analysis.knowledge_gaps),
+            len(analysis.kb_queries),
+            len(analysis.user_questions),
+        )
+
+        if usage_snapshot:
+            self._record_usage(
+                usage_snapshot,
+                analysis=analysis,
+                status="ERROR" if error_message else "SUCCESS",
+            )
+
+        return outcome
+
+    def _coerce_model(self, parsed: Any) -> Optional[PlannerAnalysisModel]:
+        if parsed is None:
+            return None
+        if isinstance(parsed, PlannerAnalysisModel):
+            return parsed
+        if isinstance(parsed, BaseModel):
+            return PlannerAnalysisModel.model_validate(parsed.model_dump())
+        if isinstance(parsed, dict):
+            return PlannerAnalysisModel.model_validate(parsed)
+        raise TypeError(f"Unsupported planner parsed payload: {type(parsed)!r}")
+
+    def _build_analysis(
+        self,
+        model: Optional[PlannerAnalysisModel],
+        reception: ReceptionResult,
+        error_message: Optional[str],
+    ) -> PlannerAnalysis:
+        if model is None:
+            fallback_goal = (reception.user_message.content or "").strip() or "Clarify the customer's request"
+            knowledge_gap = "Planner 输出解析失败，需要人工确认。"
+            user_question = "可以再详细说明一下您的目标和关键信息吗？"
+            return PlannerAnalysis(
+                status="need_more_info",
+                customer_goal=fallback_goal[:400],
+                known_facts=[],
+                knowledge_gaps=[knowledge_gap],
+                user_questions=[user_question],
+                kb_queries=[],
+                notes=error_message,
+            )
+
+        status = model.status.lower()
+        if status not in ALLOWED_STATUS:
+            status = "need_more_info"
+
+        kb_queries = [
+            KBQuery(
+                query=item.query,
+                context=item.context or "",
+                filters=item.filters or {},
+                priority=item.priority or "medium",
+            )
+            for item in model.kb_queries
+        ]
+        return PlannerAnalysis(
+            status=status,
+            customer_goal=model.customer_goal.strip(),
+            known_facts=[entry.strip() for entry in model.known_facts if entry.strip()],
+            knowledge_gaps=[entry.strip() for entry in model.knowledge_gaps if entry.strip()],
+            user_questions=[entry.strip() for entry in model.user_questions if entry.strip()],
+            kb_queries=kb_queries if self.enable_kb else [],
+            notes=(model.notes or "").strip() or None,
+        )
+
+    def _compose_debug_info(
+        self,
+        model: Optional[PlannerAnalysisModel],
+        intent: IntentDecision,
+        error_message: Optional[str],
+    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
+        debug: Dict[str, Any] = {
+            "intent_route": intent.route,
+            "intent_confidence": intent.confidence,
+            "intent_filters": intent.filters,
+        }
+        if model is not None:
+            debug["planner_raw"] = model.model_dump()
+        if error_message:
+            debug["planner_error"] = error_message
+        if intent.raw_response:
+            debug["intent_raw"] = intent.raw_response
+        return debug
+
+    def _build_messages(
+        self,
+        reception: ReceptionResult,
+        intent: IntentDecision,
+        user_story: Optional[str],
+    ) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:
+        payload = {
+            "current_user_message": {
+                "role": reception.user_message.role,
+                "content": reception.user_message.content,
+                "timestamp": reception.user_message.timestamp,
+            },
+            "historical_user_messages": [
+                {
+                    "role": msg.role,
+                    "content": msg.content,
+                    "timestamp": msg.timestamp,
+                }
+                for msg in reception.historical_user_messages[-HISTORY_SLICE:]
+            ],
+            "last_assistant_message": (
+                {
+                    "role": reception.last_assistant_message.role,
+                    "content": reception.last_assistant_message.content,
+                    "timestamp": reception.last_assistant_message.timestamp,
+                }
+                if reception.last_assistant_message
+                else None
+            ),
+            "user_story": user_story or "",
+            "intent_decision": intent.raw_response
+            or {
+                "route": intent.route,
+                "confidence": intent.confidence,
+                "filters": intent.filters,
+            },
+            "kb_allowed": self.enable_kb,
+        }
+        return [
+            {"role": "system", "content": self.system_prompt},
+            {"role": "user", "content": self._json_dumps(payload)},
+        ]
+
+    def _record_usage(
+        self,
+        usage_snapshot: Dict[str, Any],
+        *,
+        analysis: PlannerAnalysis,
+        status: str,
+    ) -> None:
+        summary = {
+            "status": analysis.status,
+            "goal": (analysis.customer_goal or "")[:80],
+            "known": len(analysis.known_facts),
+            "gaps": len(analysis.knowledge_gaps),
+            "user_questions": len(analysis.user_questions),
+            "kb_queries": len(analysis.kb_queries),
+        }
+        token_meter.record_stage(
+            label="PLANNER ANALYSIS",
+            model=usage_snapshot.get("model"),
+            prompt_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("prompt_tokens", 0),
+            completion_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("completion_tokens", 0),
+            input_text=usage_snapshot.get("input_text"),
+            output_text=usage_snapshot.get("output_text"),
+            duration_ms=usage_snapshot.get("duration_ms", 0.0),
+            status=status,
+            note=json.dumps(summary, ensure_ascii=False),
+        )
+
+    @staticmethod
+    def _json_dumps(payload: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:
+        return json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)
*** End Patch

{"output":"from __future__ import annotations

import logging

import json
from dataclasses import dataclass
from datetime import datetime, timezone
from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional

from TelegramBot.agents import AgentContext, AgentMessage, AgentOrchestrator
from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
from TelegramBot.services.redis_client import get_redis_client
from TelegramBot import token_meter
from SharedUtility.RichLogger import RichLoggerManager

RichLoggerManager.bootstrap()
logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.chat_service", level=logging.DEBUG)


@dataclass
class ConversationState:
    historical_user_messages: List[AgentMessage]
    last_assistant_message: Optional[AgentMessage]
    latest_user_message: Optional[AgentMessage]
    user_story: Optional[str]


def _now_iso() -> str:
    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(timespec="seconds")


def _serialize_message(message: AgentMessage) -> str:
    payload = {
        "role": message.role,
        "content": message.content,
        "timestamp": message.timestamp,
    }
    return json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False)


def _deserialize_message(raw: Optional[bytes]) -> Optional[AgentMessage]:
    if not raw:
        return None
    try:
        data = json.loads(raw)
        return AgentMessage(
            role=str(data.get("role", "")),
            content=str(data.get("content", "")),
            timestamp=data.get("timestamp"),
        )
    except Exception:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
        logger.debug("Failed to decode conversation payload, skipping.", exc_info=True)
        return None


class ChatService:
    """Telegram chat entrypoint backed by the OpenAI-powered agent orchestrator."""

    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self.config = get_config()
        self.history_limit = int(getattr(self.config, "telegram_history_limit", 10))
        self.context_ttl_seconds = int(getattr(self.config, "telegram_context_ttl_seconds", 3600))

        self.orchestrator = AgentOrchestrator(
            enable_kb=getattr(self.config, "kb_enabled", True),
            intent_router_enabled=getattr(self.config, "intent_router_enabled", True),
        )

        logger.info("ChatService ready with OpenAI agent orchestrator.")

    async def _load_state(
        self,
        bot_id: int,
        chat_id: int,
        user_id: int,
    ) -> ConversationState:
        client = await get_redis_client()
        history_key, last_assistant_key, latest_user_key, user_story_key = self._context_keys(bot_id, chat_id, user_id)

        pipe = client.pipeline()
        pipe.lrange(history_key, -self.history_limit, -1)
        pipe.get(last_assistant_key)
        pipe.get(latest_user_key)
        pipe.get(user_story_key)
        history_raw, last_raw, latest_raw, story_raw = await pipe.execute()

        historical_users = []
        for entry in history_raw or []:
            message = _deserialize_message(entry)
            if message:
                historical_users.append(message)

        last_assistant = _deserialize_message(last_raw)
        latest_user = _deserialize_message(latest_raw)
        if story_raw is None:
            user_story = None
        elif isinstance(story_raw, bytes):
            user_story = story_raw.decode("utf-8")
        else:
            user_story = str(story_raw)

        return ConversationState(
            historical_user_messages=historical_users,
            last_assistant_message=last_assistant,
            latest_user_message=latest_user,
            user_story=user_story,
        )

    async def _persist_state(
        self,
        *,
        bot_id: int,
        chat_id: int,
        user_id: int,
        previous_latest_user: Optional[AgentMessage],
        new_latest_user: AgentMessage,
        new_last_assistant: AgentMessage,
        user_story: Optional[str],
    ) -> None:
        client = await get_redis_client()
        history_key, last_assistant_key, latest_user_key, user_story_key = self._context_keys(bot_id, chat_id, user_id)

        pipe = client.pipeline()
        if previous_latest_user:
            pipe.rpush(history_key, _serialize_message(previous_latest_user))
        pipe.ltrim(history_key, -self.history_limit, -1)
        pipe.expire(history_key, self.context_ttl_seconds)

        pipe.set(latest_user_key, _serialize_message(new_latest_user), ex=self.context_ttl_seconds)
        pipe.set(last_assistant_key, _serialize_message(new_last_assistant), ex=self.context_ttl_seconds)

        story_value = user_story
        if story_value is not None:
            pipe.set(user_story_key, story_value, ex=self.context_ttl_seconds)
        else:
            pipe.expire(user_story_key, self.context_ttl_seconds)
        await pipe.execute()

    def _context_keys(self, bot_id: int, chat_id: int, user_id: int) -> tuple[str, str, str, str]:
        base = f"telegram:context:{bot_id}:{chat_id}:{user_id}"
        return (
            f"{base}:history",
            f"{base}:last_assistant",
            f"{base}:latest_user",
            f"{base}:user_story",
        )

    async def chat(
        self,
        bot_id: int,
        message: str,
        chat_id: int,
        user_id: int,
        username: Optional[str] = None,
        chat_type: str = "private",
    ) -> str:
        logger.info("Incoming message: bot=%s chat=%s user=%s type=%s", bot_id, chat_id, user_id, chat_type)

        token_meter.start_round(message, meta={'bot_id': str(bot_id), 'chat_id': str(chat_id), 'user_id': str(user_id), 'chat_type': chat_type or ''})

        reply_text = "Sorry, the service is temporarily unavailable. Please try again later."
        result_summary = None
        try:
            state = await self._load_state(bot_id, chat_id, user_id)

            historical_for_context = list(state.historical_user_messages)
            if state.latest_user_message:
                historical_for_context.append(state.latest_user_message)
            historical_for_context = historical_for_context[-self.history_limit :]

            current_user_message = AgentMessage(role="user", content=message, timestamp=_now_iso())

            agent_context = AgentContext.from_conversation(
                bot_id=bot_id,
                chat_id=chat_id,
                user_id=user_id,
                chat_type=chat_type,
                username=username,
                historical_user_messages=[
                    {"role": msg.role, "content": msg.content, "timestamp": msg.timestamp}
                    for msg in historical_for_context
                ],
                last_assistant_message=(
                    {"role": state.last_assistant_message.role,
                     "content": state.last_assistant_message.content,
                     "timestamp": state.last_assistant_message.timestamp}
                    if state.last_assistant_message else None
                ),
                current_user_message={
                    "role": current_user_message.role,
                    "content": current_user_message.content,
                    "timestamp": current_user_message.timestamp,
                },
                user_story=state.user_story,
            )

            outcome = await self.orchestrator.run(agent_context, message)
            reply_text = outcome.reply

            assistant_message = AgentMessage(role="assistant", content=reply_text, timestamp=_now_iso())
            updated_story = agent_context.user_story or state.user_story

            await self._persist_state(
                bot_id=bot_id,
                chat_id=chat_id,
                user_id=user_id,
                previous_latest_user=state.latest_user_message,
                new_latest_user=current_user_message,
                new_last_assistant=assistant_message,
                user_story=updated_story,
            )
            result_summary = f'\u6d88\u606f\u53d1\u9001\u6210\u529f: {len(reply_text)}\u5b57\u7b26 \u2192 chat_id={chat_id}'
        except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
            logger.error("Chat service failed: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
            result_summary = f'\u6d88\u606f\u53d1\u9001\u5931\u8d25: {exc}'
        finally:
            token_meter.end_round(
                result_summary=result_summary,
                result_text=reply_text if result_summary and result_summary.startswith('\u6d88\u606f\u53d1\u9001\u6210\u529f') else None,
            )
","metadata":{"exit_code":0,"duration_seconds":0.5}}

+from __future__ import annotations
+
+import logging
+from typing import List, Optional, Tuple
+
+from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
+
+from .base import AgentContext, KBAnswer, KBQueryBundle, PlannerAnalysis, PlannerOutcome
+from .intent_agent import IntentAgent
+from .planner_agent import PlannerAgent
+from .reception_agent import ReceptionAgent, ReceptionReplyResult
+from .visa_kb_agent import VisaKnowledgeBaseAgent
+
+logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.orchestrator", level=logging.DEBUG)
+
+FALLBACK_REPLY = "抱歉，系统暂时无法提供完整解答，已经通知人工专员跟进。"
+
+
+class AgentOrchestrator:
+    """High-level coordinator for the Telegram visa assistant stack."""
+
+    def __init__(
+        self,
+        *,
+        enable_kb: bool = True,
+        intent_router_enabled: bool = True,
+        reception_agent: Optional[ReceptionAgent] = None,
+        intent_agent: Optional[IntentAgent] = None,
+        kb_agent: Optional[VisaKnowledgeBaseAgent] = None,
+        planner_agent: Optional[PlannerAgent] = None,
+    ) -> None:
+        self.reception_agent = reception_agent or ReceptionAgent()
+        self.intent_agent = intent_agent or IntentAgent(enabled=intent_router_enabled)
+        self.kb_agent = kb_agent or VisaKnowledgeBaseAgent()
+        self.planner_agent = planner_agent or PlannerAgent(enable_kb=enable_kb)
+
+    async def run(self, context: AgentContext, user_message: str) -> Tuple[PlannerOutcome, ReceptionReplyResult]:
+        logger.info(
+            "Workflow started: bot=%s chat=%s user=%s message_preview=%s",
+            context.bot_id,
+            context.chat_id,
+            context.user_id,
+            (user_message or "").strip()[:120],
+        )
+
+        reception = await self.reception_agent.run(context, user_message)
+        logger.debug(
+            "Reception prepared context: historical=%d story=%s",
+            len(reception.historical_user_messages),
+            bool(reception.user_story),
+        )
+
+        intent = await self.intent_agent.run(context, reception)
+        logger.debug(
+            "Intent decision: route=%s confidence=%.2f needs_kb=%s",
+            intent.route,
+            intent.confidence,
+            intent.needs_kb,
+        )
+
+        if (intent.route or "").lower() == "chitchat":
+            logger.info("Intent routed to chitchat; skipping planner/kb pipeline.")
+            outcome = self._build_chitchat_outcome(reception)
+            reply = await self._safe_craft_reply(context, reception, outcome)
+            return outcome, reply
+
+        outcome = await self.planner_agent.run(context, reception, intent)
+        logger.info(
+            "Planner completed: status=%s kb_queries=%d",
+            outcome.status,
+            len(outcome.analysis.kb_queries),
+        )
+
+        kb_answers = await self._execute_kb_queries(context, reception, outcome)
+        if kb_answers:
+            outcome.kb_responses = kb_answers
+            outcome.debug_info.setdefault("kb_queries", [])
+            outcome.debug_info["kb_queries"].extend(
+                [
+                    {
+                        "query": answer.metadata.get("query"),
+                        "filters": answer.metadata.get("filters"),
+                        "answer_length": len(answer.answer or ""),
+                    }
+                    for answer in kb_answers
+                ]
+            )
+        else:
+            logger.debug("No KB answers returned for this turn.")
+
+        reply = await self._safe_craft_reply(context, reception, outcome)
+        return outcome, reply
+
+    async def _execute_kb_queries(
+        self,
+        context: AgentContext,
+        reception: "ReceptionResult",
+        outcome: PlannerOutcome,
+    ) -> List[KBAnswer]:
+        if not self.kb_agent:
+            logger.debug("KB agent disabled; skipping KB execution.")
+            return []
+
+        queries = outcome.analysis.kb_queries
+        if not queries:
+            if outcome.status == "need_more_info":
+                logger.debug("Planner needs more info but no KB queries present.")
+            return []
+
+        results: List[KBAnswer] = []
+        failures: List[dict[str, str]] = []
+        total = len(queries)
+        for index, query in enumerate(queries, 1):
+            bundle = KBQueryBundle(
+                analysis=outcome.analysis,
+                query=query,
+                index=index,
+                total=total,
+            )
+            try:
+                answer = await self.kb_agent.run(bundle=bundle, bot_key=str(context.bot_id))
+                results.append(answer)
+                logger.debug(
+                    "KB lookup #%d/%d succeeded. query_preview=%s sources=%d",
+                    index,
+                    total,
+                    (query.query or "")[:80],
+                    len(answer.sources),
+                )
+            except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
+                logger.error("KB lookup #%d failed: %s", index, exc, exc_info=True)
+                failures.append({"index": str(index), "error": str(exc)})
+
+        if failures:
+            outcome.debug_info.setdefault("kb_failures", failures)
+        return results
+
+    async def _safe_craft_reply(
+        self,
+        context: AgentContext,
+        reception: "ReceptionResult",
+        outcome: PlannerOutcome,
+    ) -> ReceptionReplyResult:
+        try:
+            reply = await self.reception_agent.craft_reply(context, reception, outcome)
+            return reply
+        except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
+            logger.error("Reception crafting failed, returning fallback reply: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
+            return ReceptionReplyResult(
+                status="error",
+                final_reply=FALLBACK_REPLY,
+                language="zh",
+                follow_ups=[],
+                meta_notes=str(exc),
+            )
+
+    def _build_chitchat_outcome(self, reception: "ReceptionResult") -> PlannerOutcome:
+        goal = reception.user_message.content.strip() or "Casual conversation"
+        analysis = PlannerAnalysis(
+            status="ok",
+            customer_goal=goal,
+            known_facts=[goal],
+            knowledge_gaps=[],
+            user_questions=[],
+            kb_queries=[],
+            notes="chitchat_route",
+        )
+        debug = {
+            "intent_route": "chitchat",
+            "chitchat": True,
+        }
+        return PlannerOutcome(analysis=analysis, status="ok", debug_info=debug)
*** End Patch

+from __future__ import annotations
+
+import json
+import logging
+from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional, Tuple
+
+from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field, ValidationError
+
+from FunctionCall_tools.visa_kb import get_tool_definitions
+from FunctionCall_tools.visa_kb.runtime import call_tool
+from TelegramBot.config.model_config import get_model_name
+from TelegramBot.config.prompt_loader import get_prompt
+from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
+from TelegramBot.openai_runtime import (
+    get_usage_snapshot,
+    parse_response,
+    parse_structured_content,
+    submit_tool_outputs,
+)
+from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
+from TelegramBot import token_meter
+
+from .base import BaseAgent, KBAnswer, KBQueryBundle, KBResponsePayload, KBSourceReference
+
+logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.kb", level=logging.DEBUG)
+
+
+class KBSourceModel(BaseModel):
+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")
+
+    path: str
+    title: Optional[str] = None
+    excerpt: Optional[str] = None
+
+
+class KBResponsePayloadModel(BaseModel):
+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")
+
+    business_summary: str
+    recommendations: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    document_checklist: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    risk_notes: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    follow_up_questions: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    sources: List[KBSourceModel] = Field(default_factory=list)
+
+
+class VisaKnowledgeBaseAgent(BaseAgent):
+    """Knowledge base agent backed by OpenAI tools for visa information."""
+
+    def __init__(self) -> None:
+        self.config = get_config()
+        self.tools = get_tool_definitions()
+        self.system_prompt = get_prompt("visa_kb.system")
+
+    async def run(self, *, bundle: KBQueryBundle, bot_key: Optional[str] = None) -> KBAnswer:
+        logger.debug(
+            "Visa KB agent invoked: index=%s/%s priority=%s query_preview=%s",
+            bundle.index,
+            bundle.total,
+            bundle.query.priority,
+            (bundle.query.query or "").strip()[:80],
+        )
+
+        usage_snapshot: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
+        tool_history: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
+        parsed_model: Optional[KBResponsePayloadModel] = None
+        error_message: Optional[str] = None
+
+        try:
+            response, usage_snapshot, tool_history, parsed_model = self._invoke_with_tools(
+                messages=self._build_messages(bundle),
+                bot_key=bot_key,
+            )
+        except ValidationError as exc:
+            logger.warning("Visa KB structured payload validation failed: %s", exc)
+            error_message = str(exc)
+        except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
+            logger.error("Visa KB agent failed: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
+            error_message = str(exc)
+
+        payload = self._convert_payload(parsed_model) if parsed_model else None
+        answer_text: Optional[str] = None
+        sources: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
+        if payload:
+            answer_text, sources = self._format_answer(payload)
+
+        metadata: Dict[str, Any] = {
+            "query": bundle.query.query,
+            "filters": bundle.query.filters,
+            "priority": bundle.query.priority,
+            "planner_goal": bundle.analysis.customer_goal,
+            "planner_status": bundle.analysis.status,
+            "tool_history": tool_history,
+        }
+        if error_message:
+            metadata["error"] = error_message
+
+        structured_dump = payload.__dict__ if payload else None
+        if payload:
+            structured_dump = {
+                "business_summary": payload.business_summary,
+                "recommendations": payload.recommendations,
+                "document_checklist": payload.document_checklist,
+                "risk_notes": payload.risk_notes,
+                "follow_up_questions": payload.follow_up_questions,
+                "sources": [
+                    {
+                        "path": src.path,
+                        "title": src.title,
+                        "excerpt": src.excerpt,
+                    }
+                    for src in payload.sources
+                ],
+            }
+
+        status = "SUCCESS" if answer_text else ("ERROR" if error_message else "WARNING")
+        if usage_snapshot:
+            self._record_usage(
+                usage_snapshot,
+                status=status,
+                answer_text=answer_text,
+                tool_count=len(tool_history),
+                bundle=bundle,
+            )
+
+        return KBAnswer(
+            answer=answer_text,
+            sources=sources,
+            metadata=metadata,
+            structured=structured_dump,
+        )
+
+    def _build_messages(self, bundle: KBQueryBundle) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:
+        payload = {
+            "planner_context": {
+                "status": bundle.analysis.status,
+                "customer_goal": bundle.analysis.customer_goal,
+                "known_facts": bundle.analysis.known_facts,
+                "knowledge_gaps": bundle.analysis.knowledge_gaps,
+                "user_questions": bundle.analysis.user_questions,
+                "notes": bundle.analysis.notes,
+            },
+            "kb_request": {
+                "query": bundle.query.query,
+                "context": bundle.query.context,
+                "filters": bundle.query.filters,
+                "priority": bundle.query.priority,
+                "index": bundle.index,
+                "total": bundle.total,
+            },
+        }
+        return [
+            {"role": "system", "content": self.system_prompt},
+            {"role": "user", "content": json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)},
+        ]
+
+    def _convert_payload(self, model: Optional[KBResponsePayloadModel]) -> Optional[KBResponsePayload]:
+        if model is None:
+            return None
+        return KBResponsePayload(
+            business_summary=model.business_summary.strip(),
+            recommendations=[item.strip() for item in model.recommendations if item.strip()],
+            document_checklist=[item.strip() for item in model.document_checklist if item.strip()],
+            risk_notes=[item.strip() for item in model.risk_notes if item.strip()],
+            follow_up_questions=[item.strip() for item in model.follow_up_questions if item.strip()],
+            sources=[
+                KBSourceReference(path=src.path, title=src.title, excerpt=src.excerpt)
+                for src in model.sources
+                if src.path
+            ],
+        )
+
+    def _invoke_with_tools(
+        self,
+        *,
+        messages: List[Dict[str, Any]],
+        bot_key: Optional[str],
+    ) -> Tuple[Any, Optional[Dict[str, Any]], List[Dict[str, Any]], Optional[KBResponsePayloadModel]]:
+        response, parsed = parse_response(
+            messages=messages,
+            model=get_model_name("visa_kb", default=self.config.openai_model, bot_key=bot_key),
+            response_format=KBResponsePayloadModel,
+            temperature=0.0,
+            usage_label="visa_kb",
+            tools=self.tools,
+        )
+        usage_snapshot = get_usage_snapshot(response)
+        tool_history: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
+
+        while getattr(response, "status", None) == "requires_action":
+            required = getattr(response, "required_action", None)
+            if not required or getattr(required, "type", None) != "submit_tool_outputs":
+                logger.warning("Unexpected required action: %s", required)
+                break
+
+            tool_calls = getattr(required.submit_tool_outputs, "tool_calls", [])
+            outputs = []
+            for call in tool_calls:
+                name = getattr(call, "name", "")
+                arguments_str = getattr(call, "arguments", "{}")
+                try:
+                    arguments = json.loads(arguments_str) if isinstance(arguments_str, str) else arguments_str
+                except json.JSONDecodeError:
+                    arguments = {}
+                result = call_tool(name, arguments or {})
+                tool_history.append(
+                    {
+                        "id": getattr(call, "id", ""),
+                        "name": name,
+                        "arguments": arguments,
+                        "result": result,
+                    }
+                )
+                outputs.append(
+                    {
+                        "tool_call_id": getattr(call, "id", ""),
+                        "output": json.dumps(result, ensure_ascii=False),
+                    }
+                )
+
+            if not outputs:
+                break
+
+            response = submit_tool_outputs(response.id, outputs, usage_label="visa_kb.tools")
+            usage_snapshot = get_usage_snapshot(response)
+            try:
+                parsed = parse_structured_content(response, KBResponsePayloadModel)
+            except Exception:
+                parsed = None
+
+        parsed_model: Optional[KBResponsePayloadModel] = None
+        if isinstance(parsed, KBResponsePayloadModel):
+            parsed_model = parsed
+        elif isinstance(parsed, BaseModel):
+            parsed_model = KBResponsePayloadModel.model_validate(parsed.model_dump())
+        elif isinstance(parsed, dict):
+            parsed_model = KBResponsePayloadModel.model_validate(parsed)
+
+        return response, usage_snapshot, tool_history, parsed_model
+
+    def _format_answer(self, payload: KBResponsePayload) -> Tuple[str, List[Dict[str, Any]]]:
+        sections: List[str] = []
+
+        if payload.business_summary:
+            sections.append(f"Business Summary:\n{payload.business_summary}")
+
+        if payload.recommendations:
+            lines = [f"{idx}. {item}" for idx, item in enumerate(payload.recommendations, 1)]
+            sections.append("Recommendations:\n" + "\n".join(lines))
+
+        if payload.document_checklist:
+            checklist = "\n".join(f"- {item}" for item in payload.document_checklist)
+            sections.append("Document Checklist:\n" + checklist)
+
+        if payload.risk_notes:
+            risks = "\n".join(f"- {item}" for item in payload.risk_notes)
+            sections.append("Risk Notes:\n" + risks)
+
+        if payload.follow_up_questions:
+            followups = "\n".join(f"- {item}" for item in payload.follow_up_questions)
+            sections.append("Follow-up Questions:\n" + followups)
+
+        sources: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
+        if payload.sources:
+            source_lines = []
+            for src in payload.sources:
+                sources.append({"path": src.path, "title": src.title, "excerpt": src.excerpt})
+                if src.title and src.excerpt:
+                    source_lines.append(f"- {src.title} ({src.path}) — {src.excerpt}")
+                elif src.title:
+                    source_lines.append(f"- {src.title} ({src.path})")
+                else:
+                    source_lines.append(f"- {src.path}")
+            sections.append("References:\n" + "\n".join(source_lines))
+
+        answer_text = "\n\n".join(section for section in sections if section).strip()
+        return answer_text or None, sources
+
+    def _record_usage(
+        self,
+        usage_snapshot: Dict[str, Any],
+        *,
+        status: str,
+        answer_text: Optional[str],
+        tool_count: int,
+        bundle: KBQueryBundle,
+    ) -> None:
+        summary = {
+            "status": status,
+            "index": bundle.index,
+            "total": bundle.total,
+            "recommendations": bundle.analysis.customer_goal,
+            "tool_calls": tool_count,
+        }
+        token_meter.record_stage(
+            label=f"KB LOOKUP #{bundle.index}",
+            model=usage_snapshot.get("model"),
+            prompt_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("prompt_tokens", 0),
+            completion_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("completion_tokens", 0),
+            input_text=usage_snapshot.get("input_text"),
+            output_text=answer_text or usage_snapshot.get("output_text"),
+            duration_ms=usage_snapshot.get("duration_ms", 0.0),
+            status=status,
+            note=json.dumps(summary, ensure_ascii=False),
+        )
*** End Patch

*** Add File: Kobe/TelegramBot/agents/reception_agent.py
+from __future__ import annotations
+
+import json
+import logging
+from datetime import datetime, timezone
+from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional
+
+from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field
+
+from TelegramBot.config.model_config import get_model_name
+from TelegramBot.config.prompt_loader import get_prompt
+from TelegramBot.config.settings import get_config
+from TelegramBot.openai_runtime import get_usage_snapshot, parse_response
+from SharedUtility.RichLogger.logger import RichLoggerManager
+from TelegramBot import token_meter
+
+from .base import AgentContext, AgentMessage, BaseAgent, PlannerOutcome, ReceptionResult
+
+logger = RichLoggerManager.for_node("telegram.reception", level=logging.DEBUG)
+
+
+def _now_iso() -> str:
+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(timespec="seconds")
+
+
+class ReceptionReplyResult(BaseModel):
+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")
+
+    status: str = Field(default="ok", pattern=r"^(ok|error|need_more_info)$")
+    final_reply: str
+    language: Optional[str] = None
+    follow_ups: List[str] = Field(default_factory=list)
+    meta_notes: Optional[str] = None
+
+
+class ReceptionAgent(BaseAgent):
+    """Reception persona responsible for greeting users and delivering final responses."""
+
+    def __init__(
+        self,
+        *,
+        max_history_messages: int = 50,
+        reply_temperature: float = 0.85,
+    ) -> None:
+        self.max_history_messages = max_history_messages
+        self.config = get_config()
+        self.reply_temperature = reply_temperature
+        self.reply_prompt = get_prompt("reception.reply")
+
+    async def run(self, context: AgentContext, user_message: str) -> ReceptionResult:
+        historical_users = (
+            context.historical_user_messages[-self.max_history_messages :]
+            if context.historical_user_messages
+            else []
+        )
+        last_assistant = context.last_assistant_message
+        current_user = context.current_user_message or AgentMessage(
+            role="user", content=user_message, timestamp=_now_iso()
+        )
+
+        history_section = self._format_history_block(historical_users)
+        last_assistant_section = self._format_message_line(last_assistant, "assistant")
+        current_section = self._format_message_line(current_user, "user", label="current")
+
+        preamble = (
+            f"now: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}\n"
+            f"user_story: {context.user_story or '(none)'}\n"
+            "historical_user_messages:\n"
+            f"{history_section}\n"
+            "last_assistant_reply:\n"
+            f"{last_assistant_section}\n"
+            "current_user_message:\n"
+            f"{current_section}"
+        )
+
+        return ReceptionResult(
+            user_message=current_user,
+            historical_user_messages=historical_users,
+            last_assistant_message=last_assistant,
+            conversation_preamble=preamble,
+            user_story=context.user_story,
+        )
+
+    async def craft_reply(
+        self,
+        context: AgentContext,
+        reception: ReceptionResult,
+        plan: PlannerOutcome,
+    ) -> ReceptionReplyResult:
+        timeline = self._build_timeline(reception)
+        timeline_block = "\n".join(timeline) if timeline else "(no recent turns)"
+
+        kb_structured = [answer.structured or {} for answer in plan.kb_responses]
+        kb_summaries = [answer.answer for answer in plan.kb_responses if answer.answer]
+
+        payload = {
+            "analysis": {
+                "status": plan.analysis.status,
+                "customer_goal": plan.analysis.customer_goal,
+                "known_facts": plan.analysis.known_facts,
+                "knowledge_gaps": plan.analysis.knowledge_gaps,
+                "user_questions": plan.analysis.user_questions,
+                "notes": plan.analysis.notes,
+            },
+            "kb_responses": kb_structured,
+            "kb_summaries": kb_summaries,
+            "latest_user_message": reception.user_message.content,
+            "conversation_timeline": timeline_block,
+        }
+
+        usage_snapshot: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
+        error_message: Optional[str] = None
+        parsed_reply: Optional[ReceptionReplyResult] = None
+
+        try:
+            response, parsed = parse_response(
+                messages=self._build_reply_messages(payload),
+                model=get_model_name("reception", default=self.config.openai_model, bot_key=str(context.bot_id)),
+                response_format=ReceptionReplyResult,
+                temperature=self.reply_temperature,
+                usage_label="reception_reply",
+            )
+            usage_snapshot = get_usage_snapshot(response)
+            parsed_reply = self._coerce_reply(parsed)
+        except Exception as exc:  # pragma: no cover - defensive
+            logger.error("Reception rewrite failed, using fallback reply: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
+            error_message = str(exc)
+
+        if parsed_reply is None:
+            parsed_reply = ReceptionReplyResult(
+                status="error",
+                final_reply="抱歉，我暂时无法完整回答您的问题，请稍后再试或联系人工客服。",
+                language="zh",
+                follow_ups=plan.analysis.user_questions,
+                meta_notes=error_message,
+            )
+
+        context.user_story = self._summarize_user_story(context, reception, plan, parsed_reply)
+        logger.debug(
+            "Reception reply ready: status=%s follow_ups=%d language=%s",
+            parsed_reply.status,
+            len(parsed_reply.follow_ups),
+            parsed_reply.language,
+        )
+
+        if usage_snapshot:
+            self._record_usage(
+                usage_snapshot,
+                reply=parsed_reply,
+                plan=plan,
+            )
+
+        return parsed_reply
+
+    def _coerce_reply(self, parsed: Any) -> Optional[ReceptionReplyResult]:
+        if parsed is None:
+            return None
+        if isinstance(parsed, ReceptionReplyResult):
+            return parsed
+        if isinstance(parsed, BaseModel):
+            return ReceptionReplyResult.model_validate(parsed.model_dump())
+        if isinstance(parsed, dict):
+            return ReceptionReplyResult.model_validate(parsed)
+        raise TypeError(f"Unsupported reception parsed payload: {type(parsed)!r}")
+
+    def _build_reply_messages(self, payload: Dict[str, Any]) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:
+        return [
+            {"role": "system", "content": self.reply_prompt},
+            {"role": "user", "content": json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)},
+        ]
+
+    def _format_message_line(
+        self,
+        message: Optional[AgentMessage],
+        speaker: str,
+        *,
+        label: str = "historical",
+    ) -> str:
+        if message is None:
+            return "  (none)"
+        timestamp = message.timestamp or "unknown"
+        return f"  - [{timestamp}] {label}.{speaker}: {message.content}"
+
+    def _format_history_block(self, messages: List[AgentMessage]) -> str:
+        if not messages:
+            return "  (none)"
+        return "\n".join(self._format_message_line(msg, "user") for msg in messages)
+
+    def _build_timeline(self, reception: ReceptionResult) -> List[str]:
+        timeline: List[str] = []
+        for msg in reception.historical_user_messages[-6:]:
+            timeline.append(self._format_message_line(msg, "user"))
+        if reception.last_assistant_message:
+            timeline.append(self._format_message_line(reception.last_assistant_message, "assistant"))
+        return timeline
+
+    def _summarize_user_story(
+        self,
+        context: AgentContext,
+        reception: ReceptionResult,
+        plan: PlannerOutcome,
+        reply: ReceptionReplyResult,
+    ) -> str:
+        pieces: List[str] = []
+        goal = plan.analysis.customer_goal.strip()
+        if goal:
+            pieces.append(f"目标: {goal}")
+
+        if plan.analysis.knowledge_gaps:
+            gaps = "; ".join(plan.analysis.knowledge_gaps[:3])
+            pieces.append(f"待补充: {gaps}")
+
+        follow_ups = reply.follow_ups or plan.analysis.user_questions
+        if follow_ups:
+            questions = "; ".join(follow_ups[:3])
+            pieces.append(f"追问: {questions}")
+
+        recommendations: List[str] = []
+        for answer in plan.kb_responses:
+            structured = answer.structured or {}
+            recommendations.extend(structured.get("recommendations", [])[:2])
+        if recommendations:
+            pieces.append("建议: " + "; ".join(recommendations[:3]))
+
+        story = " | ".join(pieces) if pieces else (reception.user_message.content[:120] or "聊天")
+        existing = context.user_story or ""
+        if existing and story:
+            combined = f"{existing} || {story}"
+            if len(combined) > 600:
+                combined = combined[-600:]
+            return combined
+        return story
+
+    def _record_usage(
+        self,
+        usage_snapshot: Dict[str, Any],
+        *,
+        reply: ReceptionReplyResult,
+        plan: PlannerOutcome,
+    ) -> None:
+        summary = {
+            "status": reply.status,
+            "analysis_status": plan.analysis.status,
+            "follow_ups": len(reply.follow_ups),
+            "knowledge_gaps": len(plan.analysis.knowledge_gaps),
+            "kb_used": len(plan.kb_responses),
+        }
+        token_meter.record_stage(
+            label="RECEPTION REPLY",
+            model=usage_snapshot.get("model"),
+            prompt_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("prompt_tokens", 0),
+            completion_tokens=usage_snapshot.get("completion_tokens", 0),
+            input_text=usage_snapshot.get("input_text"),
+            output_text=reply.final_reply,
+            duration_ms=usage_snapshot.get("duration_ms", 0.0),
+            status="SUCCESS" if reply.status == "ok" else ("WARNING" if reply.status == "need_more_info" else "ERROR"),
+            note=json.dumps(summary, ensure_ascii=False),
+        )
*** End Patch

+intent_router:
+  system: |-
+    你是 Intent Router。请根据历史消息和当前来话判断是否需要进入签证业务流程。所有输出必须是合法 JSON，字段包括：
+      - route: "business" | "chitchat" | "ambiguous"
+      - confidence: 0 到 1 的数字，保留两位小数
+      - reason: 简短中文说明（100 字以内）
+      - filters: 当 route 为 business 时给出可选的检索标签（对象或空对象 {}）
+    提供的上下文：
+      - user_story: Reception 维护的会话摘要
+      - historical_user_messages: 倒序排列的用户原话
+      - last_assistant_message: 最近一次机器人回复
+      - current_user_message: 当前用户消息
+      - conversation_preamble: Reception 拼接的摘要文本
+    决策要求：
+      1. 识别是否与签证业务相关，若涉及申请、材料、流程等操作即判定为 business。
+      2. 若信息不足以判断，route=ambiguous 并在 reason 中写明缺失要素。
+      3. 闲聊或与业务无关时 route=chitchat。
+    返回示例：
+      {"route": "business", "confidence": 0.72, "reason": "用户咨询美国 B2 续签流程", "filters": {"keywords": ["B2", "renewal"]}}
+
+planner:
+  system: |-
+    你是 Planner Agent，负责输出结构化分析结果，禁止生成客服答复。你会收到：
+      - intent_decision: 来自 Intent Router 的 JSON
+      - user_story、historical_user_messages、last_assistant_message、current_user_message
+      - kb_allowed: 是否允许调用知识库
+    请以 UTF-8 JSON（无解释文字）回复，字段定义如下：
+    {
+      "status": "ok" | "need_more_info" | "escalate",
+      "customer_goal": "概述客户的核心诉求，<=200 字",
+      "known_facts": ["已经确认的信息"],
+      "knowledge_gaps": ["需要补充的信息"],
+      "user_questions": ["需要 Reception 回问用户的问题"],
+      "kb_queries": [
+        {
+          "query": "单一主题的问题陈述，便于 KB 搜索",
+          "context": "供 KB Agent 使用的背景说明",
+          "filters": { "keywords": ["..."], "visa_type": "...", "...": "..." },
+          "priority": "high" | "medium" | "low"
+        }
+      ],
+      "notes": "可选内部提醒"
+    }
+    约束：
+      - status 必须匹配请求上下文；当缺少关键信息时使用 need_more_info。
+      - kb_queries 仅在确实需要知识库补充资料时生成；若 kb_allowed=false 则返回空数组。
+      - user_questions 与 knowledge_gaps 要对应，保持语言礼貌、简洁。
+      - 不得添加额外字段、注释或 Markdown。
+
+visa_kb:
+  system: |-
+    你是 Visa Knowledge Base Agent，负责根据 Planner 提供的上下文检索内部知识库并输出结构化方案。输出格式固定为 JSON：
+    {
+      "business_summary": "整体结论，说明适用范围与关键判断",
+      "recommendations": ["应执行的步骤，使用可操作动词开头"],
+      "document_checklist": ["需准备的材料清单"],
+      "risk_notes": ["时效或拒签风险提醒"],
+      "follow_up_questions": ["仍需向用户确认的信息"],
+      "sources": [{"path": "...", "title": "...", "excerpt": "..."}]
+    }
+    要点：
+      - 必须充分利用 planner_context 提供的 goal、known_facts、knowledge_gaps、user_questions。
+      - 推荐项保持 1-5 条，每条 <=120 字。
+      - 若未找到对应资料，请在 business_summary 中说明原因并留空 recommendations，同时补充 follow_up_questions。
+      - sources 至少包含路径 path，可选 title、excerpt。
+      - 严禁输出除 JSON 以外的内容。
+
+reception:
+  reply: |-
+    你是 Reception Persona，负责以专业、友好的语气向用户解释方案并补充追问。输入包含：
+      - analysis: Planner 的结构化分析
+      - kb_responses: 知识库返回的结构化结果数组（可能为空）
+      - kb_summaries: KB 文本摘要
+      - latest_user_message 与 conversation_timeline
+    请以 JSON 回复：
+    {
+      "status": "ok" | "need_more_info" | "error",
+      "final_reply": "发送给用户的完整话术，基于用户语言自动选择中文或英文",
+      "language": "zh" | "en" | "...",
+      "follow_ups": ["需要向用户追问的问题"],
+      "meta_notes": "可选，写给内部的说明"
+    }
+    规则：
+      1. 综合 analysis.knowledge_gaps 与 kb_responses.follow_up_questions，必要时礼貌追问。
+      2. 若无缺口且方案完整，final_reply 中给出可执行步骤和关键提醒。
+      3. 禁止输出 Markdown 或额外解释，保持 JSON 唯一根节点。
*** End Patch

*** Begin Patch
*** Add File: Kobe/TelegramBot/config/PromptStructureExample.md
+## 新版 Prompt 结构快速参考
+
+### Planner → KB → Reception 流程概览
+
+1. **Planner** 读取 `intent_decision`、历史消息等上下文，只生成结构化分析，不再产出草稿。
+2. **Visa KB Agent** 根据 Planner 提供的 `kb_queries` 逐条检索知识库，并返回结构化方案。
+3. **Reception** 汇总 Planner 分析与 KB 结果，生成最终用户话术与追问。
+
+RichLogger 在 DEBUG 级别下会输出：
+
+```
+[1st] PLANNER ANALYSIS
+[2nd] KB LOOKUP #1
+[3rd] RECEPTION REPLY
+```
+
+每个阶段的 `note` 字段都是 JSON 摘要，可直接复制调试。
+
+---
+
+### Planner 输出示例
+
+```json
+{
+  "status": "need_more_info",
+  "customer_goal": "Family of four wants to apply for US B2 visa in June.",
+  "known_facts": [
+    "Applicants hold Chinese passports",
+    "Travel purpose is tourism"
+  ],
+  "knowledge_gaps": [
+    "是否已有有效的美签记录",
+    "是否计划参加面谈"
+  ],
+  "user_questions": [
+    "您之前是否办理过美国 B1/B2 签证？",
+    "计划几月份出行？需要一起预约面谈吗？"
+  ],
+  "kb_queries": [
+    {
+      "query": "美国 B2 家庭申请流程与面谈要求",
+      "context": "首次办签，计划 6 月出行，四位家庭成员同行",
+      "filters": {"keywords": ["B2", "family", "tourism"]},
+      "priority": "high"
+    }
+  ],
+  "notes": "若有旧签证需指引续签通道"
+}
+```
+
+### Visa KB Agent 输出示例
+
+```json
+{
+  "business_summary": "美国 B2 签证适用于短期旅游或探亲。首次申请需完成 DS-160、支付 MRV 费用并预约面谈。",
+  "recommendations": [
+    "逐一填写并保存每位成员的 DS-160 表单",
+    "支付 MRV 费用后统一预约面谈日期",
+    "准备旅行计划和财力证明用于面谈说明"
+  ],
+  "document_checklist": [
+    "有效期 6 个月以上的护照",
+    "打印后的 DS-160 确认页",
+    "MRV 收据",
+    "旅行行程与酒店预订单"
+  ],
+  "risk_notes": [
+    "旺季面谈名额紧张，建议提前 6-8 周预约",
+    "若有拒签记录需准备额外说明材料"
+  ],
+  "follow_up_questions": [
+    "是否所有申请人都能在同一时间参加面谈？"
+  ],
+  "sources": [
+    {
+      "path": "kb/us/b2/introduction.md",
+      "title": "美国 B2 旅游签证手册",
+      "excerpt": "首次申请需完成 DS-160 → 支付 MRV → 安排面谈。"
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+### Reception Prompt 输入示例
+
+```json
+{
+  "analysis": {
+    "status": "need_more_info",
+    "customer_goal": "Family of four wants to apply for US B2 visa in June.",
+    "known_facts": [
+      "Applicants hold Chinese passports",
+      "Travel purpose is tourism"
+    ],
+    "knowledge_gaps": [
+      "是否已有有效的美签记录",
+      "是否计划参加面谈"
+    ],
+    "user_questions": [
+      "您之前是否办理过美国 B1/B2 签证？",
+      "计划几月份出行？需要一起预约面谈吗？"
+    ],
+    "notes": "若有旧签证需指引续签通道"
+  },
+  "kb_responses": [
+    {
+      "business_summary": "...",
+      "recommendations": ["..."],
+      "document_checklist": ["..."],
+      "risk_notes": ["..."],
+      "follow_up_questions": ["..."],
+      "sources": [{"path": "...", "title": "...", "excerpt": "..."}]
+    }
+  ],
+  "kb_summaries": [
+    "Business Summary:\n...\n\nRecommendations:\n1. ..."
+  ],
+  "latest_user_message": "我们一家四口准备暑假去美国旅游，想办 B2 签证。",
+  "conversation_timeline": "..."
+}
+```
+
+### Reception 输出示例
+
+```json
+{
+  "status": "need_more_info",
+  "final_reply": "您好！针对一家四口首次申请美国 B2 旅游签证，建议您先为每位成员完成 DS-160 表单并保留确认页，随后统一支付 MRV 费用并尽早预约同一场面谈时间。同时准备旅行计划、财力证明和家庭关系材料，以便在面谈时说明行程安排。\n\n为了给您安排更精准的步骤，还想确认两点：\n1. 您或家人是否持有仍然有效的美国签证？\n2. 预计哪一周可以安排全家一起参加面谈？\n\n收到信息后我会继续帮您细化准备事项。",
+  "language": "zh",
+  "follow_ups": [
+    "您或家人是否持有仍然有效的美国签证？",
+    "预计哪一周可以安排全家一起参加面谈？"
+  ],
+  "meta_notes": "追问原因为 Planner 标记 need_more_info。"
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+### Redis 状态同步注意事项
+
+- `user_story` 会在 Reception 阶段更新，拼接 Planner `notes`、`knowledge_gaps` 以及 KB `recommendations` 的精简摘要。
+- `latest_user_message` 永远保存最近一条用户消息；若 Planner 仍有缺口，后续轮次会继续引用。
+- 若 Reception 返回 `follow_ups`，将通过最终话术礼貌追问，不单独写入 Redis，但 `user_story` 会记录当前未完成的问题。
*** End Patch
